      • configureProvisionedServices

        protected void configureProvisionedServices()
                                     throws java.io.IOException
        Description copied from class: IntegrationTestBase
        The 'before' callback will be called after the components from IntegrationTestBase.getDependencies() have been added, but you cannot necessarily rely on injected members here. You can use the IntegrationTestBase.configure(java.lang.String, java.lang.String...) and IntegrationTestBase.configureFactory(java.lang.String, java.lang.String...) methods, as well as the IntegrationTestBase.getService(java.lang.Class<T>) methods.

        The #before callback is most useful for configuring services that have been provisioned in the 'configuration' method.

      • getDependencies

        protected org.apache.felix.dm.Component[] getDependencies()
        Description copied from class: IntegrationTestBase
        Gets a list of components that must be started before the test is started; this useful to (a) add additional services, e.g. services that should be picked up by the service under test, or (b) to declare 'this' as a component, and get services injected.
